Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.380 --> 00:00:07.420
Prof: I'm John Merriman
and this is History 202.

00:00:07.420 --> 00:00:10.926
I'm here every Monday and
Wednesday, 10:30 a.m.

00:00:10.926 --> 00:00:12.070
to 11:20 a.m.
 

00:00:12.070 --> 00:00:14.705
The way this course is,
these are all really major

00:00:14.705 --> 00:00:15.190
themes.
 

00:00:15.190 --> 00:00:17.187
I'm going to go over this a
little bit, and I'm going to

00:00:17.187 --> 00:00:18.350
talk about some of the themes.
 

00:00:18.350 --> 00:00:22.038
I kind of lecture on things
that I think that complement

00:00:22.038 --> 00:00:23.380
what you're doing.
 

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:25.070
Let me give you an example.
 

00:00:25.070 --> 00:00:28.750
When I talk about the New
Imperialism,

00:00:28.750 --> 00:00:34.816
why it is that Europe basically
took over the entire world

00:00:34.816 --> 00:00:39.085
between the 1880s and 1914,
you can read the chapter in

00:00:39.085 --> 00:00:40.520
A History of Modern
Europe,

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:44.930
which I had fun writing,
but I lecture on the Boy Scouts.

00:00:44.930 --> 00:00:47.706
I often say that I lecture on
the Boy Scouts because I was

00:00:47.706 --> 00:00:50.240
thrown out of the Boy Scouts in
Portland, Oregon,

00:00:50.240 --> 00:00:52.522
when I was a kid,
because I didn't manage to

00:00:52.522 --> 00:00:56.282
accumulate a single badge and
was totally useless after sports

00:00:56.282 --> 00:00:57.330
seasons ended.
 

00:00:57.330 --> 00:00:58.640
But that's not why I do it.
 

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:00.750
To understand the New
Imperialism,

00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:05.569
why Europe took over
essentially all of Africa,

00:01:05.569 --> 00:01:08.652
where they had places that were
totally uncharted that suddenly

00:01:08.652 --> 00:01:10.790
became highly contested between
British,

00:01:10.790 --> 00:01:16.489
French, German,
and Italian conquerors,

00:01:16.489 --> 00:01:19.590
one has to understand the
culture of imperialism.

00:01:19.590 --> 00:01:24.397
The ordinance of the Boy Scouts
in Britain has a lot to do with

00:01:24.397 --> 00:01:24.938
that.
 

00:01:24.938 --> 00:01:27.462
Why generations of British
youth and their counterparts in

00:01:27.462 --> 00:01:29.686
Germany,
and even Australia,

00:01:29.686 --> 00:01:32.610
New Zealand,
and other places,

00:01:32.610 --> 00:01:37.012
began to think that it was
important to be able to look at

00:01:37.012 --> 00:01:41.647
a map in their schoolhouse that
had the color red for Britain

00:01:41.647 --> 00:01:46.050
increasingly taking over the map
of Asia and Africa,

00:01:46.050 --> 00:01:48.110
and lots of other places as
well.

00:01:48.110 --> 00:01:49.790
So, instead of -- at the very
beginning of that lecture,

00:01:49.790 --> 00:01:51.146
I'll say, "Look,
there are three things you

00:01:51.146 --> 00:01:52.590
really ought to know about the
New Imperialism,

00:01:52.590 --> 00:01:54.650
why they did this."
 

00:01:54.650 --> 00:01:58.899
Then I talk about the Boy
Scouts, so that those two things

00:01:58.899 --> 00:02:00.390
will fit together.
 

00:02:00.390 --> 00:02:03.209
Or, when I talk about World War
I, and we'll have two lectures.

00:02:03.209 --> 00:02:06.686
My friend and colleague,
Jay Winter, is doing one of

00:02:06.686 --> 00:02:09.550
them on the Great War and modern
memory.

00:02:09.550 --> 00:02:13.038
Instead of trying to do the
entire war, and there is,

00:02:13.038 --> 00:02:16.461
I think, a quite sporty chapter
on that in the book,

00:02:16.461 --> 00:02:18.810
I'll talk about trench warfare.
 

00:02:18.810 --> 00:02:20.830
You'll see a film called
Paths of Glory.

00:02:20.830 --> 00:02:26.120
That's an early Kubrick film
about the mutinies in 1917.

00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:28.956
I'll talk about the mutinies in
1917 when people just said,

00:02:28.956 --> 00:02:30.180
"Enough is enough.
 

00:02:30.180 --> 00:02:32.360
There's no sense dying for
nothing.

00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:35.110
We won't go over the top."
 

00:02:35.110 --> 00:02:37.906
Which is to say that it's
important to come to lecture,

00:02:37.906 --> 00:02:40.030
