00:12:11.879 --> 00:12:14.450
So, of course,
I don't show that movie.

00:12:14.450 --> 00:12:14.942
I take that back.
 

00:12:14.942 --> 00:12:16.190
I don't take that back,
but what the hell.

00:12:16.190 --> 00:12:19.610
Anyway, I don't show that movie
anymore.

00:12:19.610 --> 00:12:23.364
But I do show Triumph of the
Will, and you can watch that

00:12:23.364 --> 00:12:23.960
at home.
 

00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:26.278
The other one is Au revoir
les enfants.

00:12:26.278 --> 00:12:30.206
Because one of the last
lectures I talk about resistance

00:12:30.206 --> 00:12:33.331
and collaboration in Europe,
and because I live in France

00:12:33.331 --> 00:12:37.548
much of the time,
I talk about France.

00:12:37.548 --> 00:12:39.965
Au revoir les enfants,
Goodbye Children,

00:12:39.965 --> 00:12:41.470
some of you have probably seen.
 

00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:44.868
It was made by Louis Malle,
who just died a couple of years

00:12:44.868 --> 00:12:45.220
ago.
 

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:47.556
It was about when he was in
college,

00:12:47.556 --> 00:12:50.558
so he was the equivalent of
7^(th) and 8^(th) grade.

00:12:50.558 --> 00:12:53.836
There was a new boy that shows
