00:35:31.250 --> 00:35:33.079
Caesar beat the Gauls.
 

00:35:33.079 --> 00:35:35.409
Was there not even a cook in
his army?

00:35:35.409 --> 00:35:38.510
Philip of Spain wept as his
fleet

00:35:38.510 --> 00:35:41.409
Was sunk and destroyed.
 

00:35:41.409 --> 00:35:43.480
Were there no other tears?
 

00:35:43.480 --> 00:35:48.230
Frederick the Great triumphed
in the Seven Years' War.

00:35:48.230 --> 00:35:50.349
Who triumphed with him?
 

00:35:50.349 --> 00:35:53.420
Each page a victory.
 

00:35:53.420 --> 00:35:56.829
At whose expense the victory
ball?

00:35:56.829 --> 00:36:00.179
Every ten years a great man.
 

00:36:00.179 --> 00:36:03.110
Who paid the piper?
 

00:36:03.110 --> 00:36:05.099
So many particulars.
 

00:36:05.099 --> 00:36:07.730
So many questions.
 

00:36:07.730 --> 00:36:11.980
If you hang with us this
semester, we'll get at some of

00:36:11.980 --> 00:36:12.610
those.
 

00:36:12.610 --> 00:36:14.869
See you.
 

00:36:14.869 --> 00:36:16.530
Thank you.
 

00:36:16.530 --> 00:36:18.099
Thank you.
 

